  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4774",
  "title": "fix(ts): make `CSSClasses` types consistent",
  "body": "**Summary**\r\n\r\nIn some cases, we were exporting our `CSSClasses` types as required for our widgets, while they are in reality optional and partial.\r\n\r\nTo avoid our users to provide extra logic over our types and to keep it consistent with our usage, the types are now:\r\n- Exported as optional in the widget.\r\n- Export as required in the component.\r\n\r\n**Result**\r\n\r\n- The exported types are now correct.\r\n- When a component is provided, its `CSSClasses` type will be in the same file, named `FootComponentCSSClasses`\r\n\r\n**Next step**\r\n\r\n- Provide the same update to the `templates` types\r\n\r\n**Ticket**\r\n\r\n[DX-1644](https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/DX-1644)",
